uk.co.strangeskies.utility

Class Isomorphism.Mapping

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.utility.Isomorphism.Mapping
  • Enclosing class:
    Isomorphism

    public class Isomorphism.Mapping
extends Object
    The main API surface for interacting with the Isomorphism, represents a mapping according to a given key equality.

      • getPartialMapping

        public <S,C> S getPartialMapping(C node,
                                 BiFunction<C,Consumer<Supplier<S>>,S> mapping)
        Make a mapping of the given node, or fetch an existing mapping if one has been made via this Isomorphism.

        In the case of recursive graph structures we sometimes may need access to a partially constructed mapping, as we may revisit a node during the construction of its own mapping.

        Once the mapping is calculated, the partial result will be removed from the isomorphism, and future attempts to map the node will return the complete result, though often the two references will be identity equal.

        Type Parameters:
        S - the type of the node
        C - the type of the result
        Parameters:
        node - the graph node to map
        mapping - the mapping function to apply, also accepting a consumer which can be called back with a partial result
        Returns:
        a mapping of the given node

                                 Supplier<S> partial,
                                 Function<C,S> mapping)
        Make a mapping of the given node, or fetch an existing mapping if one has been made via this Isomorphism.

        In the case of recursive graph structures we sometimes may need access to a partially constructed mapping, as we may revisit a node during the construction of its own mapping.

        Once the mapping is calculated, the partial result will be removed from the isomorphism, and future attempts to map the node will return the complete result, though often the two references will be identity equal.

        Type Parameters:
        S - the type of the node
        C - the type of the result
        Parameters:
        node - the graph node to map
        partial - a partial mapping to use until the proper mapping is computed
        mapping - the mapping function to apply, also accepting a consumer which can be called back with a partial result
        Returns:
        a mapping of the given node
